> These, friends, are not your ordinary pork chops. In fact, our chefs gave 'em a steak-like treatment, transforming the everyday protein into something extraordinary. The tender chops are coated in steak spice, seared, then drizzled with a creamy pan sauce. Like any great steakhouse-style meal, the sides are just as impressive. Roasted potatoes and zesty green beans round everything out. Now all you need is someone to bring you a dessert menu!

== Roasted Potatoes & Lemony Green Beans ==

Adjust rack to top position (top and middle positions for 4 servings) and preheat oven to 425 degrees. Wash and dry produce.

Dice @Yukon Gold Potatoes{12%ounce} into ½-inch pieces. Halve, peel, and mince @Yellow Onion{1/2}(peeled and minced). Zest and quarter @Lemon{1}.

Toss potatoes on one side of a #baking sheet{} with a drizzle of @cooking oil{2%teaspoon}, @salt{}, and @pepper{}.

> For 4 servings, spread potatoes out across entire sheet; roast for 20-25 minutes total.

Roast on top rack for ~{10%minutes} (you'll add the green beans then).

Trim @Green Beans{6%ounce} if necessary.

Once potatoes have roasted ~{10%minutes}, remove baking sheet from oven. Carefully toss green beans on empty side with a drizzle of oil, salt, and pepper.

> For 4 servings, leave potatoes roasting and add green beans to a second baking sheet; roast on middle rack.

Return to top rack until potatoes are golden brown and green beans are tender, ~{10-15%minutes} more.

== Steak and Pan Sauce ==

While veggies roast, pat @Beef Tenderloin Filets{10%ounce} dry with paper towels; season all over with salt, then coat with as much @Bold & Savory Steak Spice{1%tablespoon} as will stick.

> Swap in beef for pork; cook to desired doneness, 4-7 minutes per side.

Heat a drizzle of @olive oil{2%teaspoon} in a large pan over medium-high heat. Add pork and cook until browned and cooked through, ~{4-6%minutes} per side.

> TIP: If crust begins to brown too quickly, reduce heat to medium.

Turn off heat; transfer pork to a #plate{}. Wipe out pan.

Heat a drizzle of olive oil in same pan over medium heat. Add minced onion; cook, stirring, until softened and lightly browned, ~{3-4%minutes}.

Stir in @Beef Stock Concentrate{1} and @water{1/4%cup}. Bring to a simmer and cook until slightly reduced, ~{2-3%minutes}.

Remove from heat and stir in @Sour Cream{2%tablespoon} until combined. Season generously with pepper.

Toss green beans with lemon zest.

Divide pork, potatoes, and green beans between plates. Spoon pan sauce over pork. Serve with lemon wedges on the side.